(275, 2, '2016-11-27 16:42:32', '2016-11-27 16:42:32', 'Not a complicated relationship story, <strong>Gauri Shinde</strong> is a women director with tons of creative thoughts. Dear Zindagi movie is a fabulously scripted story beeline, which visually displays the physiological pain a person goes through when he/she falls in a blind love.\r\n\r\nDD is a gag word used in the movie for \"<strong>Dimag Ka Doctor</strong>\" narrated character by <strong>Shahrukh Khan</strong>, a handsome love broken man, who solves<strong> Alia Bhat\'s</strong> mental illness with his unique &amp; smart ideas, which you will better know if you watch the movie yourself.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_270\" align=\"alignright\" width=\"300\"]<img class=\"size-medium wp-image-270\" src=\"http://www.maikalaal.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Dear-Zindagi-review-Must-read-300x225.jpg\" alt=\"Dear ZIndagi Movies reviews on mai ka laal\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" /> Dear Zindagi Movies reviews on mai ka laal[/caption]\r\n\r\nAlia Bhat, a cinematographer, in the movie fed up with his consistent way  of profession and wants to capture some role in a huge project, Kunal Kapoor, a smoking hot dude also a non-committed boyfriend of Kyra (Alia) was one of the three so-called friend zone guys.\r\n\r\nThe audience loves Alia Bhat mischief behavior and after a long time, the folks are going to adore the charm of KING Khan, which he failed to do in few of his prior about to be huge hit movies.\r\n\r\nThe magic spell of Dear Zindagi is going to motivate you anyhow. Parenthood is an another major issue presented on the screen boldly.\r\n\r\nIn the film, Shahrukh is played a charming therapist,, while Alia Bhatt is a damaged insomniac. Dear Zindagi bravely tries to ease the stigma around mental health and that is  an important conversation to have,  which I like the most in the film .At one point, he (Shahrukh)  tells kaira ( alia) \" Don\'t let your past blackmail your present to ruin a beautiful future \" and another one \"hartoothichijjoodijasktihai\".<wbr />.\r\nThe another admiral thing about the film is its attempt to root out the stigma attached to mental health and shame associated with therapy. Love You Zindagi!11!!! Keep calm &amp; move steadfastly.', 'Dear Zindagi review: Alia bhatt a help seeker, Shahrukh directed by Gauri Shinde', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '260-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-11-27 16:42:32', '2016-11-27 16:42:32', '', 260, 'http://www.maikalaal.com/260-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
